parts.text:
```json
{
"application": "rMATS",
"details": {
"dependencies": [
"rMATS 4.1.2",
"STAR 2.7.6a",
"jq"
],
"resources": [
"lscratch (250GB)",
"CPU (32 cores per task)",
"Memory (64GB)",
"Time (8 hours)"
],
"input_files": [
"groups.tab",
"contrasts.tab",
"Reports/multiqc_matrix.tsv",
"config.json",
"*.R1.fastq.gz",
"*.R2.fastq.gz"
],
"output_files": [
"rMATS/STAR/2.7.6a/genes-*/",
"rMATS/*/s1.txt",
"rMATS/*/s2.txt",
"rMATS/*_v_*/"
],
"description": "This script automates the running of rMATS for differential splicing analysis on RNA-seq data. It takes a RNA-seq output directory as input, and requires two additional files: 'groups.tab' and 'contrasts.tab'. The script uses these files to generate a sample sheet and then submits jobs to run rMATS for each comparison defined in the 'contrasts.tab' file. The script also builds a STAR index for the genome if necessary."
}
}
```
